festival 2019: full list of films |work=The Guardian |accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> Shortly after, [[Sony Pictures Classics]] acquired distribution rights to the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/the-climb-movie-cycling-comedy-sony-classics-deal-cannes-1202622085/|title=Sony Classics Acquires Un Certain Regard Buddy Comedy \u2018The Climb\u2019 \u2013 Cannes|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|date=May 24, 2019|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref> The film went onto screen at the [[Telluride Film Festival]] on August 30, 2019,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/telluride-film-festival-2019-lineup-ford-vs-ferrari-judy-full-list-of-movies-1202706577/|title=Telluride Film Festival: \u2018Ford V Ferrari\u2019, \u2018Judy\u2019, \u2018Motherless Brooklyn\u2019, Weinstein-Inspired Drama \u2018The Assistant\u2019 Among Premieres Headed to 46th Edition \u2013 Full List|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Pete|last=Hammond|date=August 29, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> The [[Toronto International Film Festival]] on September 6, 2019,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/aeronauts-burnt-orange-heresy-join-tiff-2019-lineup-1231031|title='The Aeronauts,' 'Burnt Orange Heresy' Added to Toronto Film Fest Lineup|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|date=August 13, 2019|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tiff.net/events/the-climb|title=The Climb|website=[[Toronto International Film Festival]]|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref> and the [[Sundance Film Festival]] on January 24, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundance.org/projects/the-climb-3d1157ca-7585-4795-884c-945641173bac|title=The Climb|website=[[Sundance Film Festival]]|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt was scheduled to be released on March 20, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/video/the-climb-trailer-cannes-feature-1202198306/|title=\u2018The Climb\u2019 Trailer: